    "subject": "Remove the 100 m/s delay before firing",
    "description": "hatcher reported a 100 m/s before firing. Apparently, this is done to keep animations in sync?\r\nShooting is a core-mechanic in any shooter game, so an intentional delay on that mechanic doesn't seem wise.\r\n\r\nThere is an old thread about this here: http://forums.warchest.com/showthread.php/7912-Trivia-weapon-delay-between-pressing-button-and-firing\r\n\r\n\r\n>// these defines are matched with the character torso animations\r\n>#define DELAY_LOW\t\t100\t// machineguns, tesla, spear, flame\r\n>#define DELAY_HIGH\t\t100\t// mauser, garand\r\n>#define DELAY_PISTOL\t100\t// colt, luger, sp5, cross\r\n>#define DELAY_SHOULDER\t50\t// rl\r\n>#define DELAY_THROW\t\t250\t// grenades, dynamite\r\n",
